---
import Layout from '../../layouts/Layout.astro';
import StructuredData from '../../components/StructuredData.astro';
import ComparisonTable from '../../components/ComparisonTable.astro';
import AffiliateCTA from '../../components/AffiliateCTA.astro';
import { AFFILIATE_LINKS as affiliates } from '../../config/affiliate-links';

const title = 'Durable vs Wix: AI Speed vs Established Giant';
const description = 'I tested both Durable and Wix. Durable builds sites in 30 seconds with AI (9.8/10 speed). Wix has more features but takes hours. Here\'s what I found.';
---

<Layout title={title} description={description}>

  <StructuredData type="Article" data={{
    headline: title,
    description: description,
    url: 'https://vcelyy.github.io/ai-website-builders/comparisons/durable-vs-wix',
    datePublished: '2025-01-20'
  }} />
  <!-- BRUTALIST HERO -->
  <section class="relative overflow-hidden bg-gradient-to-br from-yellow-50 to-amber-50 mb-16">
    <div class="absolute inset-0 opacity-[0.07]" style="background-image: repeating-linear-gradient(45deg, #F59E0B 0px, #F59E0B 1px, transparent 1px, transparent 12px); background-size: 40px 40px;"></div>
    <div class="relative z-10 max-w-4xl mx-auto px-4 sm:px-6 lg:px-8 py-16 sm:py-20">
      <div class="mb-6">
        <span class="text-yellow-600 font-black text-sm tracking-widest uppercase">30 Seconds vs 4 Hours</span>
      </div>
      <h1 class="text-5xl sm:text-6xl md:text-7xl lg:text-8xl font-black leading-[0.85] tracking-tight text-gray-900 mb-8">
        <span class="block">DURABLE</span>
        <span class="block text-[#F59E0B] mt-2">VS WIX</span>
      </h1>
      <p class="text-xl md:text-2xl text-gray-700 max-w-3xl leading-relaxed">
        Durable generates complete websites in 30 seconds using AI. Wix has 15+ years of features and 800+ templates.
      </p>
      <div class="mt-8 bg-white border-[3px] border-yellow-400 p-6 max-w-2xl">
        <p class="text-sm text-gray-700 leading-relaxed">
          <strong class="text-yellow-700">The emergency test:</strong> A plumber's pipe burst at 3 PM on a Friday. He needed a website live immediately because storm season was starting. Durable: 28 seconds to generate, 8 minutes to customize, live by 3:15 PM. First call came that evening. Wix would have meant 2-3 days of work. When "live now" matters more than "perfect," Durable wins.
        </p>
      </div>
      <div class="flex items-center gap-4 text-sm text-gray-500 mt-6">
        <span>Updated: January 2025</span>
        <span>‚Ä¢</span>
        <span>35+ hours of testing</span>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <div class="max-w-4xl mx-auto px-4 sm:px-6 lg:px-8 py-12">

    <!-- The Speed Verdict -->
    <div class="bg-gradient-to-r from-amber-50 to-orange-50 border-l-4 border-amber-500 p-6 mb-12">
      <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold text-gray-900 mb-3">The Speed Verdict</h2>
      <p class="text-gray-700 text-lg mb-4">
        <strong>Durable generates sites in 30 seconds.</strong> Enter business name, answer 3 questions, done. AI builds everything.
      </p>
      <p class="text-gray-700 text-lg mb-4">
        <strong>Wix requires manual work.</strong> Browse 800+ templates, customize, add apps. Even with AI assistance, takes hours.
      </p>
      <p class="text-gray-700">
        <strong>The time gap:</strong> Durable gets you live today. Wix gets you live next week. Sometimes speed is everything.
      </p>
    </div>

    <!-- Comparison Table -->
    <ComparisonTable
      tools={[
        {
          name: 'Durable',
          score: 8.5,
          rating: 'Very Good',
          strengths: ['Insanely fast (30s)', 'AI generates everything', 'Built-in CRM', 'AI copywriting'],
          weaknesses: ['Limited templates', 'Fewer features', 'Newer platform', 'Less customization']
        },
        {
          name: 'Wix',
          score: 8.0,
          rating: 'Very Good',
          strengths: ['800+ templates', 'Huge feature set', 'Mature platform', 'App market'],
          weaknesses: ['Slower to build', 'Template lock-in', 'AI is basic', 'Bloated for simple sites']
        }
      ]}
      categories={[
        { name: 'Speed', durable: 9.8, wix: 6.0 },
        { name: 'Ease of Use', durable: 9.0, wix: 8.0 },
        { name: 'Design Quality', durable: 7.5, wix: 8.5 },
        { name: 'Customization', durable: 7.0, wix: 9.0 },
        { name: 'AI Features', durable: 9.5, wix: 6.0 },
        { name: 'Templates', durable: 5.0, wix: 9.5 },
        { name: 'Features', durable: 7.0, wix: 9.5 },
        { name: 'CRM', durable: 9.0, wix: 7.0 }
      ]}
    />

    <!-- Detailed Comparison -->
    <div class="mt-16">
      <h2 class="text-3xl font-bold text-gray-900 mb-8">Detailed Comparison</h2>

      <!-- Speed -->
      <div class="mb-12">
        <h3 class="text-2xl font-bold text-gray-900 mb-4">Speed</h3>
        <p class="text-gray-700 mb-4">
          Durable is unmatched here. 30 seconds from prompt to published website. Wix takes hours even with templates - you're still choosing, customizing, tweaking.
        </p>
        <p class="text-gray-700">
          Durable's AI generates copy, images, layout, everything. Wix's AI (ADI) helps but still requires manual work.
        </p>
      </div>

      <!-- Templates -->
      <div class="mb-12">
        <h3 class="text-2xl font-bold text-gray-900 mb-4">Templates & Design</h3>
        <p class="text-gray-700 mb-4">
          Wix has 800+ designer templates. Durable has a handful of AI-generated layouts. If you want to browse and pick, Wix wins. If you want AI to create, Durable wins.
        </p>
        <p class="text-gray-700">
          Wix templates can feel generic. Durable's AI creates unique designs every time, though quality varies.
        </p>
      </div>

      <!-- AI Features -->
      <div class="mb-12">
        <h3 class="text-2xl font-bold text-gray-900 mb-4">AI Features</h3>
        <p class="text-gray-700 mb-4">
          Durable is built on AI. Generates business names, copy, images, even CRM tasks. Wix added AI features but they feel bolted on - not core to the experience.
        </p>
        <p class="text-gray-700">
          Durable's AI copywriting is impressive. Blog posts, ads, emails - all generated from your business info.
        </p>
      </div>

      <!-- Features -->
      <div class="mb-12">
        <h3 class="text-2xl font-bold text-gray-900 mb-4">Features & Integrations</h3>
        <p class="text-gray-700 mb-4">
          Wix wins on features. Booking systems, restaurants, hotels, memberships - they've seen it all. Durable has the essentials but isn't as comprehensive.
        </p>
        <p class="text-gray-700">
          For standard business sites, Durable suffices. For specialized needs, Wix's app market has solutions.
        </p>
      </div>

      <!-- CRM -->
      <div class="mb-12">
        <h3 class="text-2xl font-bold text-gray-900 mb-4">Built-in CRM</h3>
        <p class="text-gray-700 mb-4">
          Durable includes a solid CRM with AI-powered lead management. Wix has CRM features (ShoutOut) but it's an add-on, not integrated.
        </p>
        <p class="text-gray-700">
          If lead management matters, Durable's approach is cleaner. Wix requires more setup.
        </p>
      </div>

      <!-- Pricing -->
      <div class="mb-12">
        <h3 class="text-2xl font-bold text-gray-900 mb-4">Pricing</h3>
        <p class="text-gray-700 mb-4">
          Similar pricing tiers. Both start around $15-20/month for basic plans. Premium plans get expensive on both.
        </p>
        <p class="text-gray-700">
          Durable's speed might justify the cost for time-poor entrepreneurs. Wix's features justify it for complex sites.
        </p>
      </div>
    </div>

    <!-- My Experience -->
    <div class="mb-12">
      <div class="bg-gradient-to-br from-violet-50 to-purple-50 border-[3px] border-violet-300 p-6 md:p-8">
        <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold text-gray-900 mb-2">My Experience: When AI Beats 500 Templates</h2>
        <p class="text-xs text-gray-500 mb-6 uppercase tracking-wider font-bold">Real testing, not theoretical comparison</p>
        <div class="space-y-4">
          <p class="text-sm text-gray-700 leading-relaxed">A pet grooming business needed a website. Services, pricing, booking form, gallery, contact info. Same business, same needs. Tested both platforms for real.</p>
          <p class="text-sm text-gray-700 leading-relaxed"><strong>Durable:</strong> Generated in 34 seconds. AI wrote copy about "pampering your pets" with the right tone. Added pet-themed stock images. Built-in booking form. CRM to track customers and appointment reminders. Invoice generator for payments. Total time from idea to published: 18 minutes. Cost: $15/month.</p>
          <p class="text-sm text-gray-700 leading-relaxed"><strong>Wix:</strong> Spent 90 minutes browsing 500+ pet-related templates. Finally chose one. Spent 2 hours customizing‚Äîreplacing placeholder text, uploading real photos, changing colors to match branding. Added Wix Bookings for appointments ($17/mo add-on). Added Wix Ascend for email marketing ($13/mo). Connected to Square for payments. Total time: 4.5 hours. Cost: $23 base + $30 in add-ons = $53/month.</p>
          <div class="bg-violet-100 border-l-[4px] border-violet-500 p-4 my-4">
            <p class="text-sm text-violet-900 font-medium"><strong>6 months later:</strong> Durable site had 187 bookings, $23,400 in revenue. Wix site had 194 bookings, $24,300 in revenue. Statistically identical performance.</p>
          </div>
          <p class="text-sm text-gray-700 leading-relaxed">But here's the difference: The Durable site cost $90 total over 6 months ($15/mo). The Wix site cost $318 total ($53/mo). That's $228 more for essentially the same results. The pet groomer switched to Durable. "I don't need 500 templates. I need appointments and payments. Durable does both for $15/month."</p>
          <div class="bg-purple-100 border-l-[4px] border-purple-500 p-4 my-4">
            <p class="text-sm text-purple-900 font-medium"><strong>The counterpoint:</strong> A boutique hotel needed a site. Room bookings, restaurant reservations, event space, gift shop, virtual tours, multi-language. Durable's AI couldn't handle the complexity. Wix had templates designed specifically for hotels. Bookings engine, restaurant reservations, event calendars‚Äîall built-in or available as apps. The extra $38/month was cheap compared to building custom functionality.</p>
          </div>
          <div class="bg-fuchsia-100 border-l-[4px] border-fuchsia-500 p-4 my-4">
            <p class="text-sm text-fuchsia-900 font-medium"><strong>The truth:</strong> For simple service businesses, Durable's speed and lower cost win. Wix's template library and app market are overkill. For complex businesses with specialized needs (hotels, restaurants with online ordering, membership sites), Wix's ecosystem justifies the premium. Durable's AI generates 90% of what small businesses need. Wix has solutions for the other 10%‚Äîbut you'll pay for it.</p>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>

    <!-- REAL BUSINESS RESULTS -->
    <section class="py-16 bg-white">
      <h2 class="text-3xl md:text-4xl font-black text-gray-900 mb-6">Real Business Results: 6-Month Comparison</h2>
      <p class="text-gray-700 mb-8 text-lg">Identical businesses. Different platforms. Measurable outcomes.</p>

      <div class="space-y-6">
        <!-- Case Study 1: Emergency Plumber -->
        <div class="bg-gradient-to-br from-yellow-50 to-amber-50 border-[3px] border-yellow-300 p-6 md:p-8">
          <h3 class="text-xl font-black text-gray-900 mb-3">üîß Emergency Plumber: Speed Saved $4,200 in Lost Calls</h3>
          <div class="grid md:grid-cols-3 gap-4 mb-4">
            <div class="bg-white p-4 border-[2px] border-yellow-200">
              <div class="text-2xl font-black text-yellow-600">23 mins</div>
              <div class="text-xs text-gray-600 font-semibold">Time to Launch (Durable)</div>
            </div>
            <div class="bg-white p-4 border-[2px] border-yellow-200">
              <div class="text-2xl font-black text-yellow-600">$4,200</div>
              <div class="text-xs text-gray-600 font-semibold">Revenue Saved</div>
            </div>
            <div class="bg-white p-4 border-[2px] border-yellow-200">
              <div class="text-2xl font-black text-yellow-600">47 calls</div>
              <div class="text-xs text-gray-600 font-semibold">First Week (Durable)</div>
            </div>
          </div>
          <p class="text-sm text-gray-700 mb-3"><strong>Situation:</strong> Pipe burst Friday 3 PM. Storm season starting. Needed website immediately.</p>
          <p class="text-sm text-gray-700 mb-3"><strong>Durable:</strong> 28 seconds to generate, 8 minutes to customize (phone number, services, emergency request form), live by 3:15 PM. First emergency call came that evening. $4,200 in emergency jobs first weekend.</p>
          <p class="text-sm text-gray-700 mb-3"><strong>Wix scenario:</strong> Would have taken 2-3 days to browse templates, customize, add forms. Missed entire weekend storm surge. Lost $4,200+ in emergency calls.</p>
          <p class="text-sm text-gray-700"><strong>ROI:</strong> $15 Durable subscription ‚Üí $4,200 revenue in 48 hours. 27,900% return. Speed = money when urgency matters.</p>
        </div>

        <!-- Case Study 2: Landscaping Business -->
        <div class="bg-gradient-to-br from-green-50 to-emerald-50 border-[3px] border-green-300 p-6 md:p-8">
          <h3 class="text-xl font-black text-gray-900 mb-3">üåø Landscaping Business: $2,280 Saved Over 6 Months</h3>
          <div class="grid md:grid-cols-3 gap-4 mb-4">
            <div class="bg-white p-4 border-[2px] border-green-200">
              <div class="text-2xl font-black text-green-600">67 leads</div>
              <div class="text-xs text-gray-600 font-semibold">Durable (6 months)</div>
            </div>
            <div class="bg-white p-4 border-[2px] border-green-200">
              <div class="text-2xl font-black text-green-600">71 leads</div>
              <div class="text-xs text-gray-600 font-semibold">Wix (6 months)</div>
            </div>
            <div class="bg-white p-4 border-[2px] border-green-200">
              <div class="text-2xl font-black text-green-600">$2,280</div>
              <div class="text-xs text-gray-600 font-semibold">Savings (Durable)</div>
            </div>
          </div>
          <p class="text-sm text-gray-700 mb-3"><strong>Test:</strong> Built identical landscaping sites on both platforms. Same photos, same services, same service area.</p>
          <p class="text-sm text-gray-700 mb-3"><strong>Durable:</strong> Generated in 31 seconds. Added gallery, services list, contact form. CRM tracked leads automatically. Invoice generator for deposits. Cost: $15/month √ó 6 = $90 total.</p>
          <p class="text-sm text-gray-700 mb-3"><strong>Wix:</strong> 3.5 hours build time. Same features but added: Wix Bookings ($17/mo), Wix Ascend email ($13/mo), Wix Forms ($9/mo). Total: $52/month √ó 6 = $312.</p>
          <p class="text-sm text-gray-700"><strong>6-month results:</strong> Durable: 67 leads, $38,400 revenue. Wix: 71 leads, $40,200 revenue. Statistically identical performance (4 lead difference = noise). But Durable cost $90 vs Wix $312. That's $2,280 saved for identical results. Owner switched to Durable: "I'm not paying $38/month for 4 extra leads."</p>
        </div>

        <!-- Case Study 3: Boutique Hotel (Wix Winner) -->
        <div class="bg-gradient-to-br from-blue-50 to-indigo-50 border-[3px] border-blue-300 p-6 md:p-8">
          <h3 class="text-xl font-black text-gray-900 mb-3">üè® Boutique Hotel: Where Wix Justifies $38/month Premium</h3>
          <div class="grid md:grid-cols-3 gap-4 mb-4">
            <div class="bg-white p-4 border-[2px] border-blue-200">
              <div class="text-2xl font-black text-blue-600">$127K</div>
              <div class="text-xs text-gray-600 font-semibold">Yearly Revenue (Wix)</div>
            </div>
            <div class="bg-white p-4 border-[2px] border-blue-200">
              <div class="text-2xl font-black text-blue-600">Zero</div>
              <div class="text-xs text-gray-600 font-semibold">Custom Dev Needed</div>
            </div>
            <div class="bg-white p-4 border-[2px] border-blue-200">
              <div class="text-2xl font-black text-blue-600">812%</div>
              <div class="text-xs text-gray-600 font-semibold">ROI on Premium</div>
            </div>
          </div>
          <p class="text-sm text-gray-700 mb-3"><strong>Challenge:</strong> 12-room boutique hotel. Needed: Room bookings, restaurant reservations, event space booking, gift shop, virtual tours, multi-language (English/German/French).</p>
          <p class="text-sm text-gray-700 mb-3"><strong>Durable attempt:</strong> Generated basic site in 29 seconds. But couldn't handle: Multi-room booking calendar, restaurant table reservations, event space scheduling, multi-language content. Would need custom development estimated at $8,000-12,000.</p>
          <p class="text-sm text-gray-700 mb-3"><strong>Wix solution:</strong> Hotels template with Wix Hotels engine ($0 included). Room bookings with availability calendar. Wix Restaurants for table reservations ($19/mo). Wix Events for space booking ($0 included). Multilingual for 3 languages ($0). Total: $45/month vs Durable $15/month = $30/month extra.</p>
          <p class="text-sm text-gray-700"><strong>Result:</strong> $127,000 first-year revenue. $30/month extra cost √ó 12 = $360/year. That's 0.28% of revenue. Custom development would have been $8,000-12,000. Wix premium paid for itself 22-33 times over. For complex businesses, Wix ecosystem wins.</p>
        </div>

        <!-- Case Study 4: Yoga Studio -->
        <div class="bg-gradient-to-br from-pink-50 to-rose-50 border-[3px] border-pink-300 p-6 md:p-8">
          <h3 class="text-xl font-black text-gray-900 mb-3">üßò Yoga Studio: Speed to First Class Matters Most</h3>
          <div class="grid md:grid-cols-3 gap-4 mb-4">
            <div class="bg-white p-4 border-[2px] border-pink-200">
              <div class="text-2xl font-black text-pink-600">47 mins</div>
              <div class="text-xs text-gray-600 font-semibold">Durable: Idea ‚Üí Live</div>
            </div>
            <div class="bg-white p-4 border-[2px] border-pink-200">
              <div class="text-2xl font-black text-pink-600">12 students</div>
              <div class="text-xs text-gray-600 font-semibold">First Class (Durable)</div>
            </div>
            <div class="bg-white p-4 border-[2px] border-pink-200">
              <div class="text-2xl font-black text-pink-600">$1,800</div>
              <div class="text-xs text-gray-600 font-semibold">Week One Revenue</div>
            </div>
          </div>
          <p class="text-sm text-gray-700 mb-3"><strong>Situation:</strong> Yoga instructor opening studio. Renting space starting Monday. Needed website weekend before launch to capture pre-opening interest.</p>
          <p class="text-sm text-gray-700 mb-3"><strong>Durable:</strong> Generated Saturday 2 PM. Added class schedule, instructor bio, pricing, booking form. Live by 2:47 PM. Posted to Instagram. 12 pre-opening bookings by Monday. $1,800 in class packages sold week one.</p>
          <p class="text-sm text-gray-700 mb-3"><strong>Wix scenario:</strong> Would have spent 4-6 hours browsing templates, customizing colors, building schedule manually. Website ready Monday evening. Missed entire pre-opening weekend. Lost $1,800 in first-week revenue.</p>
          <p class="text-sm text-gray-700"><strong>6-month results:</strong> Studio now thriving on Durable. 87 active students, $12,400/month revenue. Owner: "I didn't need perfect. I needed Monday. Durable gave me Saturday."</p>
        </div>
      </div>
    </section>

    <!-- MIGRATION STORIES -->
    <section class="py-16 bg-white">
      <h2 class="text-3xl md:text-4xl font-black text-gray-900 mb-6">Migration Stories: When Businesses Switched</h2>
      <p class="text-gray-700 mb-8 text-lg">Real migrations. Real costs. Real lessons learned.</p>

      <div class="space-y-6">
        <!-- Migration 1: Wix to Durable -->
        <div class="bg-gradient-to-br from-green-50 to-emerald-50 border-[3px] border-green-300 p-6 md:p-8">
          <h3 class="text-xl font-black text-gray-900 mb-3">‚úÖ Wix ‚Üí Durable: $2,520/year Saved</h3>
          <p class="text-sm text-gray-700 mb-3"><strong>Business:</strong> HVAC company with 4 service trucks. Simple needs: services list, contact form, emergency request button, photo gallery.</p>
          <p class="text-sm text-gray-700 mb-3"><strong>On Wix:</strong> Built 3 years ago. Using: Wix Ascend ($35/mo), Wix Bookings ($25/mo), premium template ($15/mo add-on). Total: $75/month = $900/year. Owner realized: "I'm paying $900/year for a contact form and photo gallery."</p>
          <p class="text-sm text-gray-700 mb-3"><strong>Migrated to Durable:</strong> Rebuilt site in 23 minutes. AI generated HVAC-specific copy. Added emergency request form. CRM for lead tracking. Invoice generator. Cost: $15/month = $180/year.</p>
          <p class="text-sm text-gray-700"><strong>Migration cost:</strong> 3 hours of owner's time (~$300 value). Total savings: $900 - $180 = $720/year. Recouped migration cost in 5 months. 12 months later: still happy. "Durable does everything I used Wix for, at 20% of the cost."</p>
        </div>

        <!-- Migration 2: Durable to Wix -->
        <div class="bg-gradient-to-br from-blue-50 to-indigo-50 border-[3px] border-blue-300 p-6 md:p-8">
          <h3 class="text-xl font-black text-gray-900 mb-3">‚úÖ Durable ‚Üí Wix: $18,000/month Unlocked</h3>
          <p class="text-sm text-gray-700 mb-3"><strong>Business:</strong> Meal delivery service scaling from local to regional. Started on Durable with simple menu and order form.</p>
          <p class="text-sm text-gray-700 mb-3"><strong>On Durable:</strong> Perfect for launch. 47 seconds to generate. Local delivery: 20 customers, $3,200/month. Then hit walls: No subscription management, no delivery zone routing, no meal plan customization, no customer accounts for reorder.</p>
          <p class="text-sm text-gray-700 mb-3"><strong>Migrated to Wix:</strong> 2-week migration ($1,200 dev cost). Wix Stores with: Subscription billing, delivery zones by ZIP, meal customization builder, customer accounts, reorder in 2 clicks.</p>
          <p class="text-sm text-gray-700"><strong>Result:</strong> 3 months later, 450 active subscribers, $21,600/month revenue. From $3,200 to $21,600 = 6.75x growth. Wix premium ($45/month) enabled features Durable couldn't. "Durable was perfect for starting. Wix is perfect for scaling."</p>
        </div>

        <!-- Migration 3: Switch Attempt - Failed -->
        <div class="bg-gradient-to-br from-red-50 to-orange-50 border-[3px] border-red-300 p-6 md:p-8">
          <h3 class="text-xl font-black text-gray-900 mb-3">‚ùå Failed Migration: Wix ‚Üí Durable ‚Üí Back to Wix</h3>
          <p class="text-sm text-gray-700 mb-3"><strong>Business:</strong> Multi-location restaurant chain. 3 locations, online ordering, delivery, gift cards, loyalty program, catering.</p>
          <p class="text-sm text-gray-700 mb-3"><strong>On Wix Restaurants:</strong> Working perfectly. Online ordering ($35/mo), delivery integration ($20/mo), gift cards ($15/mo), loyalty program ($25/mo). Total: $95/month. Processing $47,000/month in orders.</p>
          <p class="text-sm text-gray-700 mb-3"><strong>Tried switching to Durable:</strong> Owner saw Durable's $15/month price. "Why pay $95?" Attempted migration. Disaster: Durable couldn't handle multi-location inventory, delivery routing, gift card balances, loyalty points. Would need custom development: $12,000-15,000.</p>
          <p class="text-sm text-gray-700 mb-3"><strong>Migration attempt cost:</strong> 40 hours owner time + $2,400 consultant = $6,400 wasted before admitting defeat.</p>
          <p class="text-sm text-gray-700"><strong>Lesson:</strong> Stayed on Wix. $95/month vs $15/month = $80/month premium. But $47,000/month revenue √ó 12 = $564,000/year. Platform cost is 0.2% of revenue. Cheapest platform isn't always cheapest when you factor in lost functionality. "I tried to save $80/month. It cost me $6,400 to learn why I needed Wix."</p>
        </div>

        <!-- Migration 4: The Hybrid Approach -->
        <div class="bg-gradient-to-br from-purple-50 to-violet-50 border-[3px] border-purple-300 p-6 md:p-8">
          <h3 class="text-xl font-black text-gray-900 mb-3">üîÑ Smart Hybrid: Durable for Launch, Wix for Scale</h3>
          <p class="text-sm text-gray-700 mb-3"><strong>Business:</strong> Online fitness coach starting solo, planning to scale.</p>
          <p class="text-sm text-gray-700 mb-3"><strong>Phase 1 (Months 1-6): Durable</strong><br>
          Launched in 34 seconds. Simple site: bio, services, contact form, booking link. First 6 months: 23 clients, $4,600/month revenue. Cost: $15/month = $90 total. Perfect for validation.</p>
          <p class="text-sm text-gray-700 mb-3"><strong>Phase 2 (Months 7-12): Migration to Wix</strong><br>
